    <content>&lt;b&gt; NBER Working Papers&lt;/b&gt; &lt;br&gt;A foundational question in General Equilibrium theory—when is an equilibrium stable?—has remained largely unresolved for over 150 years despite important contributions. This paper proposes a resolution.</content>
